message.content: Salvia columbariae is a species of flowering plant in the Lamiaceae family. It is commonly known as chia sage or golden chia. The plant typically grows to around 1 meter in height. The leaves are silver-green and the flowers are violet-blue in color. The flowers bloom between March and June. The seeds of Salvia columbariae have been historically used as a food source by indigenous people in California. It can commonly be found in desert regions of southwestern United States and northern Mexico.
